names.fullName: NDRG1 coimmunoprecipitates beta-catenin and E-cadherin from LNCaP cell lysate

attributeList.attribute: 2 B

This complex formed when LNCaP cells were androgen-stimulated or -deprived. NDRG1 is dramatically increased after R1881 treatment but levels of E-cadherin and beta-catenin in the NDRG1-IP complex did not increase after exposure to R1881.

names.fullName: NDRG1 coimmunoprecipitates CANX from LNCaP cell lysate

attributeList.attribute: 2 E

The level of Ku70 and CANX in the IP complex was extremely low compared to the supernatant. It was not possible to detect NDRG1 in the IP complexes when the IP was performed using anti-Ku70 or anti-CANX antibodies. This is likely due to there being free forms of Ku70 and CANX.
